n><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">RCH0020</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Supplementary written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">British Association of Social Workers</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">(</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">BASW</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Background</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">At the Oral Session on 6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> November 2013, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">BASW was asked to make proposals concerning the qualifications and training of local authority staff engaged in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">identifying and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">commissioning a placement for children’s residential care.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The background t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">o this </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">request</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> was that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, in BASWs view, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as the private sector has become increasingly the majority provider of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Children’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Residential Care, it has become </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">increasingly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">important for local authorities to employ staff to identify and commission quality </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">provision</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and to maximise the information available to Social Workers about the experience and everyday culture about a variety of provision</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> for looked after children. It is also becoming more important that Social Workers involved in placing children, an</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d supporting children in placement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> have an understanding of commissioning processes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">BASW believes the qualification and experience of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">staff involved in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Commissioning and placement </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">identification</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and providing background support to front-line Social Work</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> are crucial in getting the right placement at the right time for the right child. This is an area where a high level of skill is required.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> We advocate that such Teams should be led by a qualified Social Worker and staff with residential and fostering e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">xperience and skills should be key members of such teams</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, particularly in terms of setting out the key elements of a contracted placement and the contract monitoring of the placement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">As well as some commissioning staff having Social Work (SW) qualificatio</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ns, this is also about front line staff having training and development and an understanding of the commissioning processes and what their part in it is. There may be a choice of services so they would really need to understand what would deliver the best </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">outcomes for that child. Then when a service is selected they would need to understand how they would know whether the service was delivering improvement which would relate back to the individual assessment of need and changing needs over time. </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Similarly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the provider would need to know what they are expected to deliver which will be quality assured by the operational Social Worker and Commissioning monitoring staff.  For services commissioned outside the Local Authority, the feedback from referring Social </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Workers needs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to be fed into the formal contract meetings, this again requires time and trained and experienced Commissioning and contract staff.  A combination of SWs definition of outcomes and these being communicated to the provider and defined within a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n agreement or contract should be the mechanism for ensuring quality and ultimately good outcomes for children and young people. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Currently, the organisation of Commissioning and placements teams appear to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">vary both</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in nature of membership </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> terms of staff qualification and training. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Team membership</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> varies and may include Social Workers, Contracting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">staff,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> staff with history of residential or foster </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">care-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> or the placement finding activity in some authorities may be seen as more of an administ</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rative function. There appears to be little consistency between local authorities.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In 2009 Skills for Care and CWDC worked in all four UK countries to develop National Occupational Standards (NOS) for Commissioning, contracting and procurement of social ca</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">re, and in 2013 this , we understand is being revised by Skills for Care. BASW has consistently supported the development of these NOS, but are very disappointed that we cannot find evidence of the NOS substantially being put into practice by local authori</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ties or education institutions , at least as far as children’s services are concerned.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">BASW believes key elements </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for a training and qualification structure for Commissioning and Placement support are:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Children’s Placement and Commissioning Teams to be led</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> by someone with a qualification</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in Social Work </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">with Post Qualifying specialist training on Commissioning and placement planning- perhaps Level 5 of the National Occupational Standards </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Other staff should have a  Certificate of Commissioning based on the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">N</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">OS</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Social Workers , as part of their training, need to have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">an understanding and knowledge base of integrated c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ommissioning and placement issues</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">All staff, including placing Social Workers, need to have:</span></li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">An understanding of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">integrated </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">commissioning process</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">es</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to support good outcomes and value for money within the context of services commissioned across LA and health</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Experience of commissioning and quality assuring individual and service requests for children</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">An understanding of the S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ocial Work rol</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e in the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">commissioning process</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Ability to apply commissioning principles to work with children and families</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Commitment to focus on the ‘individual’ needs of the child in social work practice</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Understanding of evidence based programmes</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>